Definitions


"Software" means VRS and all materials covered by this license.

"Project" means a game, application, simulation, educational work, or other work that uses or incorporates the Software.

"Commercial Use" means use intended to produce revenue, compensation, commercial advantage, funding, or business value, including use in paid products, advertisements, subscriptions, in-app purchases, client work, contract work, company projects, internal business tools, or projects intended for future commercial release.

"Author" means Ilia Zherlitsin.

"Protected Portions" means the literal source code, header files, algorithms, and architectural implementation details of the Software as expressed in the official VRS repository — that is, the specific expression of the code itself. Protected Portions do not include: public API names, function signatures, or interfaces necessary for interoperability; general concepts, ideas, or design patterns (e.g., "a layered stat-modifier resolution system") that are not tied to VRS's specific implementation; or any functionality independently arrived at without copying, viewing for the purpose of copying, or adapting VRS's source expression.

"Publicly Available" means accessible by any person who is not (a) the Author, (b) a member of a Project team under the "Permitted Non-Commercial Use" section, or (c) an authorized contributor acting under the "Contributions" section, without requiring specific individual permission from the Author. A private repository or distribution list is not Publicly Available merely because it has more than one member, provided access remains restricted to persons described in (b) or (c).


