Projects Using VRS


A Project that merely uses, links against, calls, subclasses, or integrates with the public APIs of VRS is not automatically considered a modified version or source-code derivative work of VRS.

A modified version or source-code derivative work means a work that copies, modifies, adapts, or incorporates Protected Portions of the VRS source code.

This license does not prohibit independently developed software merely because it has similar features, systems, APIs, or purposes, provided that it does not copy or derive from Protected Portions of the Software.


Repository Forks


A public fork of the official VRS repository may be used only for:


Viewing, studying, evaluating, or testing the Software.
Preparing and submitting contributions to the official repository.


Modified VRS source code may be published in a public fork only to the extent reasonably necessary to prepare or submit a contribution.

Personal modifications not intended for contribution must be kept locally or in a private, non-Publicly-Available repository.

A fork may not be used to:


Maintain or distribute an independent version of VRS.
Publish releases or downloadable builds of VRS.
Provide VRS or a modified version to third parties for separate use.
Publish a competing or replacement product based on Protected Portions of VRS.
Avoid obtaining a required commercial license.


Every fork must preserve this license and all applicable legal notices.

Rights granted directly by GitHub or another hosting platform for use of that platform remain subject to the applicable platform terms. Such platform rights do not grant permission to use or distribute the Software beyond this license.


